research_municipality_step.notes: Laredo, Texas, operates under a council-manager system, where the elected city council, including the mayor, serves as the primary legislative body. The mayor is elected at large, and eight council members are elected from single-member districts. Mayor Victor Treviño assumed office in 2022. Council Members Ricardo 'Rick' Garza (District IV), Ruben Gutierrez, Jr. (District V), and Vanessa Perez (District VII) were sworn in on January 2, 2025.
